WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:02.170 --> 00:00:04.951
Professor Ben Polak:
Okay, so I want to set up a new

00:00:04.951 --> 00:00:07.588
topic today, and to get us
started I thought we'd play a

00:00:07.588 --> 00:00:09.540
game.
So the game is going to be

00:00:09.540 --> 00:00:12.580
called cash in a hat,
and we'll see what this game is

00:00:12.580 --> 00:00:14.316
like in a minute.
So the idea is this,

00:00:14.316 --> 00:00:15.250
there's going to be two
players.

00:00:15.250 --> 00:00:18.952
I'm going to pick on two of you.
I hope I can find people who

00:00:18.952 --> 00:00:24.393
brought some money to class.
So Player I will have a choice,

00:00:24.393 --> 00:00:29.750
Player I can put nothing,
$1 or $3 into a hat.

00:00:29.750 --> 00:00:34.841
The hat will then be given to
Player II and Player II can look

00:00:34.841 --> 00:00:40.350
at what's in the hat and either
she can match what's in the hat,

00:00:40.350 --> 00:00:46.402
i.e., add the same amount in so
1 if it's 1, or 3 if it's 3,

00:00:46.402 --> 00:00:49.890
or she can simply take the
cash.

00:00:49.890 --> 00:00:52.370
The payoffs of this game will
be as follows.

00:00:52.370 --> 00:00:54.826
Player I, if they put nothing
in, they're not going to get

00:00:54.826 --> 00:00:57.248
anything.
If they put 1 in and it's

00:00:57.248 --> 00:01:01.770
matched then they double their
money, so they get 2 back.

00:01:01.770 --> 00:01:06.016
If they put 3 in and it's
matched then they double their

00:01:06.016 --> 00:01:09.489
money, so they get 6 back so
they'll net 3.

00:01:09.489 --> 00:01:14.078
However, if they put 1 in and
Player II takes it they've just

00:01:14.078 --> 00:01:17.367
lost their dollar,
and if they put $3 in and

00:01:17.367 --> 00:01:20.350
Player II takes it they've lost
$3.

00:01:20.350 --> 00:01:22.310
Everyone understand that?
Pretty simple.

00:01:22.310 --> 00:01:27.941
From Player II's point of view,
if Player II matches then they

00:01:27.941 --> 00:01:32.925
get their investment back plus
$1.50 if they matched 1,

00:01:32.925 --> 00:01:38.503
so the get 2.50 back in all;
and they get their investment

00:01:38.503 --> 00:01:43.660
back plus $2 if they match 3,
so they get 5 back in all.

00:01:43.660 --> 00:01:46.401
Of course, if they simply take
the money out of the hat and put

00:01:46.401 --> 00:01:49.010
it in their pocket then that's
what they get in the game.

00:01:49.010 --> 00:01:51.940
So once again,
if Player II matches with $1,

00:01:51.940 --> 00:01:56.096
there's $1 in the hat and she
matches, then she gets back 2.50

00:01:56.096 --> 00:02:00.011
for a profit of 1.50.
If there's $3 and she matches

00:02:00.011 --> 00:02:02.909
3, she gets back 5 for a profit
of 2;

00:02:02.909 --> 00:02:06.783
and if she simply takes the
money out of the hat and puts it

00:02:06.783 --> 00:02:11.050
in her pocket then she gets how
ever much money was in the hat.

00:02:11.050 --> 00:02:15.738
So I here will be the provider
of the hat, we'll use the same

00:02:15.738 --> 00:02:18.746
